race.comment: THE CRIMSON PIRATE (1) was close to a maiden win on a number of occasions last campaign, including in Saturday grade prior to the break. His recent trial was very good and this trip first-up shapes nicely. Maps well and looks to have found a very winnable race if he can pick up from where he left off. MOONWALK (7) got a long way back on resumption and was just steady in the run to the line. She'll be better for that run however and Pike hopping in the saddle is a good push for her chances. Up in trip should suit and a much better run is on the cards. WATTO'S WARRIOR (5) will find this a little easier than what he faced last time out when 3.6L off the winner. Still a maiden taking on CL1's, but stepping out in trip may hold the key and a forward showing is on the cards. WINNING SHUFFLE (4) is better than he showed last start and can bounce back. Ditto AITCH MONTANA (6) whose maiden win two starts ago stacks up in this field.
